President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate William G. Dauster and Richard E. Zuckerman to key positions in his Administration. Dauster is nominated to be a Member of the Board of Trustees of the Federal Supplementary Medical Insurance Trust Fund, the Federal Hospital Insurance Trust Fund, and the Federal Old-Age and Survivors Insurance Trust Fund and the Federal Disability Insurance Trust Fund. Zuckerman is nominated to be an Assistant Attorney General (Tax Division). He currently serves as the Principal Deputy Assistant Attorney General for the Tax Division at the Department of Justice. President Trump has also announced his intent to appoint several individuals as Members of the Federal Salary Council.